# SEO Rules

## Page-Level Requirements
- Unique `<title>` per page (50-60 chars, keyword-first, brand at end)
- Unique `<meta name="description">` per page (150-160 chars, compelling CTA)
- Single `<h1>` per page containing primary keyword
- Sequential heading hierarchy (h1→h2→h3, no level skips)
- Semantic HTML5 elements (article, section, nav, main, aside, footer)

## Technical SEO
- Canonical URL on every page (`<link rel="canonical">`)
- Open Graph tags (og:title, og:description, og:image, og:url)
- Twitter Card tags (twitter:card, twitter:title, twitter:description)
- Structured data (JSON-LD Schema.org) for page type
- XML sitemap at /sitemap.xml
- robots.txt allowing crawling of important paths

## Performance (Core Web Vitals)
- LCP < 2.5s — optimize hero images, preload critical fonts
- CLS < 0.1 — set width/height on images, font-display: swap
- INP < 200ms — defer non-critical JS, debounce inputs

## GEO (Generative Engine Optimization)
- Start with direct answer, then explain
- Use clear headings and bullet points
- Include statistics with sources
- FAQ sections with question + direct answer
- Comprehensive topic coverage

